definition: to complement/to make up for a deficiency
to repair/to patch/to mend/to make up for/to fill (a vacancy)/to supplement

sentences.english: Some records, make up the history books of the palace.
sentences.chinese: 有些記載，彌補了史書之闕。

sentences.english: So why is there not a third party that fills the gap?
sentences.chinese: 所以，爲什麼沒有第三黨來彌補這中間的差距？

sentences.english: It is impossible for me to recoup.
sentences.chinese: 叫我來彌補損失是不可能的。

sentences.english: Jones redeemed his earlier poor performance by scoring two goals .
sentences.chinese: 瓊斯射入兩球方彌補其初時表現之不足。

sentences.english: Fiber reinforced concrete can make up for the brittleness of concrete.
sentences.chinese: 纖維增強混凝土可以彌補一般混凝土的脆性缺陷。

sentences.english: What he lacks in speed he makes up for in strength.
sentences.chinese: 他的力量彌補了他速度的不足。

sentences.english: Losses of the PBC shall be setoff by allocations of the central finance.
sentences.chinese: 中國人民銀行的虧損由中央財政撥款彌補。

sentences.english: But next year, tax rises will make up nearly half of it.
sentences.chinese: 但明年，稅收的增長將會彌補一半縮減的開支。

sentences.english: In the end, a substantial transfer from Saudi Arabia closed the gap.
sentences.chinese: 最終，由沙特阿拉伯劃撥的大量資金彌補了這一差額。

sentences.english: He wanted to do a time recording equipment, a good make up for lack of a sundial.
sentences.chinese: 他就想再做一件記時器具，好彌補日晷的不足。

sentences.english: Good one, connecting product advertising communication staying power shortage.
sentences.chinese: 好處一，彌補產品廣告傳播後勁的不足。

sentences.english: He tried to atone for his rudeness by sending her flowers.
sentences.chinese: 他想送些鮮花給她來彌補自己的粗魯無禮。

sentences.english: Hourly billing serves both of these ends.
sentences.chinese: 以小時計費很好的彌補了雙方的短板。

sentences.english: That drag has been more or less fully offset by the boost from net trade.
sentences.chinese: 淨貿易的增加或多或少彌補了這一負面影響。

sentences.english: Whatever you've done couldn't atone for the misdeeds.
sentences.chinese: 無論你做什麼，都不能彌補過去的罪行。

sentences.english: Of course, they bring unique benefits that compensate for the restrictions.
sentences.chinese: 當然，它們帶來的獨特益處足以彌補這些限制。

definition: to fill a gap/to fill in a blank (on a form)/to overcome a deficiency
to settle (a dispute)/to resolve/to solve/to dispose of/to dispatch
to lead to/to create/to cause/to bring about
to break away from/to cast off (old ideas etc)/to get rid of/to break away (from)/to break out (of)/to free oneself from/to extricate oneself
to display/to exhibit/to bring out implicit or innate qualities/to express (a thought or moral)/to develop (an idea)/to elaborate (on a theme)
